# {{.ProjectName}}

Claude plugin generated by [plugin-kit-ai](https://github.com/plugin-kit-ai/plugin-kit-ai) `init`.

## Status

- Runtime: `go`
- Status: `production-ready`, stable default path
- Bootstrap contract: Go `1.22+`

Choose this lane when long-term support, packaged distribution, and the clearest release story matter more than matching an existing interpreted runtime.

## First Run

```bash
go mod edit -replace=github.com/777genius/plugin-kit-ai/sdk=<absolute-path-to>/sdk/plugin-kit-ai
go test ./...
go build -o bin/{{.ProjectName}} ./cmd/{{.ProjectName}}
plugin-kit-ai validate . --platform claude --strict
```

## Stable Default

- `Stop`
- `PreToolUse`
- `UserPromptSubmit`

The scaffold wires only the public-stable Claude hook subset by default.

Use `plugin-kit-ai init <name> --platform claude --claude-extended-hooks` when you intentionally want the full runtime-supported hook set scaffolded.

## Target Files

- `targets/claude/hooks/hooks.json`: authored Claude hook routing
- `hooks/hooks.json`: rendered managed Claude hook file
- Optional first-class Claude breadth via `--extras`:
  - `targets/claude/settings.json` -> rendered `settings.json`
  - `targets/claude/lsp.json` -> rendered `.lsp.json`
  - `targets/claude/user-config.json` -> rendered `plugin.json.userConfig`
  - `targets/claude/manifest.extra.json` -> manifest passthrough for non-managed keys only

If you move the project, update the authored hook command paths so they still point at `{{.Entrypoint}}`.
Keep stdout reserved for Claude responses and write diagnostics to stderr only.
